Six people sustained injuries on Monday when a taxi rear-ended a bus at the Royal Park and Columbine Road intersection in Mondeor, south of Johannesburg.ER24 on scene on Columbine and Royal park, Mondeor. Six injured in bass and taxi collision. @help24JHB @ewnupdates @eNCA @JacaNews pic.twitter.com/sQLPQsHBoy ER24 EMS (Pty) Ltd. (@ER24EMS) April 24, 2017On arrival paramedics found the taxi and bus on the left-hand lane of the road. The taxi was found crushed against the rear of the bus.Two men trapped inside the taxi while four other walking around on the scene.ER24 Spokesperson Russel Meiring said &#8220;Rescue service had to use specialized rescue tools to extricate both men from the vehicle. Once freed, paramedics found that both men had sustained serious injuries while four others had sustained minor to moderate injuries&#8221;.All the patients were treated and later transported to Baragwanath Hospital for further treatment.Fortunately, from the bus no one sustained any injuries.Local authorities are investigating the cause of the collision.-TNA Reporter 